---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import batteryTrim from '../assets/pitch-trim-battery.png';
import sensorCoverage from '../assets/lidar-coverage.png';
import cameraCoverage from '../assets/camera-coverage.png';
import batteryPack from '../assets/battery-pack-assembly.jpeg';
import lidarTest from '../assets/lidar-scan-test.png';
import buoyDetection from '../assets/buoy-detection.png';
import rollTrim from '../assets/roll-trim-outriggers.png';
import gimbalDrawing from '../assets/lidar-gimbal-drawing.png';
import frontLidarMount from '../assets/front-lidar-mount.png';
import operatorConsole from '../assets/operator-console.jpg';

const loops = [
  {
    number: '01',
    title: 'Pitch',
    body: 'The 1.8 kWh battery slides fore and aft on rails, shifting the centre of mass.',
  },
  {
    number: '02',
    title: 'Roll',
    body: 'Linear actuators in the outriggers adjust the righting moment in real time.',
  },
  {
    number: '03',
    title: 'Sensors',
    body: 'A custom-built gimbal holds the front lidar level through any residual motion.',
  },
];

const features = [
  {
    title: 'Pitch trim by weight shift',
    eyebrow: 'Stabilisation · Loop 01',
    images: [
      {
        image: batteryTrim,
        alt: 'Cutaway render showing the battery sliding fore and aft inside the main hull',
      },
    ],
    dark: true,
    body: [
      'Instead of relying on hull shape alone, Ligmax keeps itself level mechanically. The 1.8 kWh battery — the heaviest component on board — slides fore and aft on linear rails, driven by a dual-shaft stepper and belt, moving the centre of mass to trim pitch.',
      'The battery does double duty as energy store and trim mass, so the stabilisation costs almost no extra weight — and trimming the vessel to the right attitude to plane cuts wetted area and drag at speed.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Roll trim by active outriggers',
    eyebrow: 'Stabilisation · Loop 02',
    images: [
      {
        image: rollTrim,
        alt: 'Render of the outriggers shifting vertically to counter roll',
      },
    ],
    dark: true,
    body: [
      'Linear actuators shift the outriggers vertically, adjusting the righting moment and the immersion of the main hull to counter roll — augmenting the passive stability of the wide trimaran stance with active control.',
      'The result is a vessel that stays composed in wake and chop, exactly when precision matters most: docking, station-keeping and threading a buoy channel.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'A custom gimbal for the front lidar',
    eyebrow: 'Stabilisation · Loop 03',
    images: [
      {
        image: frontLidarMount,
        alt: 'Close-up render of the gimbal-stabilised front lidar mounted in the carbon-fibre bow',
      },
    ],
    dark: true,
    body: [
      'The third loop guards perception directly. The front 360° lidar rides on a compact gimbal designed and built in-house — just over 100 mm across — with its own dedicated IMU for fast, local correction. Whatever pitch and roll remain after the hull-level loops, the gimbal cancels, holding the scan plane horizontal at all times.',
      'A 2D lidar sees a single slice of the world, so that slice has to be the right one. Keeping it level means buoys stay in view scan after scan instead of vanishing as the bow lifts — recovering the robustness of a far heavier, more expensive 3D sensor rig from an inexpensive 2D unit.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Object detection, straight from geometry',
    eyebrow: 'Sensing & autonomy',
    images: [
      {
        image: sensorCoverage,
        alt: 'Top-down visualisation of the 360-degree lidar coverage around the vessel',
      },
    ],
    dark: true,
    body: [
      'Two 360° lidars — one gimbal-stabilised at the bow, one aft — give continuous range data on every bearing. A deterministic Euclidean clustering algorithm groups the scan returns into candidate objects, each with a range, bearing and size: fast, explainable detection with no training data required.',
      'Deterministic geometry is the backbone of a safety-critical vehicle — every detection can be traced back to the exact points that produced it.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Cameras add what lidar cannot: colour',
    eyebrow: 'Sensing & autonomy',
    images: [
      {
        image: cameraCoverage,
        alt: 'Visualisation of the usable forward field of view of the two wide-angle cameras',
      },
    ],
    dark: true,
    body: [
      'Lidar is colour-blind, and the course is not — channel buoys are red and green. Two 220° wide-angle cameras cover the whole forward arc, and a probabilistic classifier projects each lidar detection into the camera frame and samples its colour, labelling objects without a single neural weight.',
      'As a fallback and cross-check, a YOLO26L detection network runs on dedicated vision hardware — an NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano Super — finding buoys directly in the image even in difficult light. Geometry from lidar, colour from camera, verified by the network.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'A ground station built for zero hesitation',
    eyebrow: 'Operations',
    images: [
      {
        image: operatorConsole,
        alt: 'The Ligmax operator console showing live camera feed with buoy detection, minimap, lidar world model and safety-critical telemetry',
      },
    ],
    dark: true,
    body: [
      'The operator console is custom software, matured on the team’s earlier 5G-controlled UGV project. A UDP hole-punched connection runs directly between vessel and laptop over 5G — no relay, no cloud — for the lowest latency physically achievable, carrying live camera feeds, the lidar world model and full telemetry.',
      'Picking up a game controller takes over manual control instantly, with no menus in between, and a lightweight web dashboard gives judges and team an at-a-glance view. Kill and hold commands are always one action away — mirrored on an independent long-range RC link in case 5G drops.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Resilient systems & safety',
    eyebrow: 'Engineering for the water',
    images: [
      {
        image: batteryPack,
        alt: 'The 12S12P lithium-ion battery pack during assembly',
      },
    ],
    dark: false,
    body: [
      'Safety-critical control is deliberately separated from autonomy: a Pixhawk 6C flight controller owns hard-real-time control and failsafes, while a Raspberry Pi 5 and an NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano Super run planning and perception. All propulsion power routes through a physical emergency-stop safety loop.',
      'The self-built battery lives in a fireproof aluminium-and-steel enclosure with full BMS telemetry, the hull seals with an interlocked powered lid, and three bilge pumps keep the vessel operational even after water ingress. A direct 5G link carries operator video and telemetry, with an independent long-range RC link as backup.',
    ],
  },
];

const evidence = [
  {
    image: lidarTest,
    alt: 'Live 2D lidar scan plotted during workshop testing',
    caption: 'Live lidar scan during workshop bench testing',
  },
  {
    image: buoyDetection,
    alt: 'Camera image of a green buoy on open water with a detection bounding box',
    caption: 'CNN buoy detection validated on open water',
  },
  {
    image: gimbalDrawing,
    alt: 'Technical drawing of the custom front-lidar gimbal',
    caption: 'Custom front-lidar gimbal, designed in-house',
    light: true,
  },
];
---

<section class="section" id="technology">
  <div class="container">
    <div data-reveal>
      <span class="eyebrow">Technology</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Attacking instability at the source</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        Most student vessels accept wave motion and try to clean up the data in software. Ligmax holds the
        boat — and its sensors — level mechanically, with three coordinated control loops, each closed
        around live IMU feedback.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="loops" data-reveal>
      {loops.map((loop) => (
        <li class="loop-card">
          <span class="loop-number">{loop.number}</span>
          <h3>{loop.title}</h3>
          <p>{loop.body}</p>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>

    <div class="features">
      {features.map((feature, index) => (
        <article class:list={['feature', { 'feature--flip': index % 2 === 1 }]} data-reveal>
          <div class:list={['feature-media', { 'feature-media--dark': feature.dark }]}>
            {feature.images.map((item) => (
              <figure class="media-figure">
                <Image
                  src={item.image}
                  alt={item.alt}
                  widths={[480, 720, 960]}
                  sizes="(max-width: 900px) 92vw, 520px"
                />
                {item.caption && <figcaption>{item.caption}</figcaption>}
              </figure>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="feature-copy">
            <span class="feature-eyebrow">{feature.eyebrow}</span>
            <h3>{feature.title}</h3>
            {feature.body.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
          </div>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="build" data-reveal>
      <div class="build-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">The build</span>
        <h3 class="build-title">Built from parts, not kits</h3>
        <p class="build-lead">
          Ligmax is not an assembled product — it is 31 numbered line items turned into a vessel. The hull is
          3D-printed in sections and hand-laminated in carbon fibre; the 144-cell battery pack is welded
          in-house and enclosed in its own fireproof box; rails, belts, actuators, drivers and compute are
          wired and integrated by the team.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn--primary build-cta" href="/build">See every component</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="evidence" data-reveal>
      <h3 class="evidence-title">Validated in the lab &mdash; headed for the water</h3>
      <p class="evidence-lead">
        Every subsystem has been integrated and bench-tested. Pool trials and full-course testing against
        real buoys in Trondheim and Oslo complete the campaign ahead of the competition.
      </p>
      <ul class="evidence-grid">
        {evidence.map((item) => (
          <li>
            <figure>
              <div class:list={['evidence-media', { 'evidence-media--light': item.light }]}>
                <Image
                  src={item.image}
                  alt={item.alt}
                  widths={[420, 640]}
                  sizes="(max-width: 700px) 92vw, 350px"
                />
              </div>
              <figcaption>{item.caption}</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .loops {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.8rem) 0 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .loop-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    padding: 1.4rem 1.5rem 1.3rem;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--brand);
  }

  .loop-number {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .loop-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .loop-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .features {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .feature {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .feature--flip .feature-media {
    order: 2;
  }

  .feature-media {
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    background: var(--bg-soft);
  }

  .feature-media--dark {
    background:
      radial-gradient(30rem 18rem at 50% 42%, rgba(120, 158, 224, 0.2), transparent 70%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--navy-900), var(--navy-800));
    border-color: var(--navy-800);
  }

  .feature-media {
    display: grid;
  }

  .media-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .feature-media--dark .media-figure + .media-figure {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  }

  .media-figure figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    padding: 0.15rem 1rem 0.8rem;
  }

  .feature-media--dark .media-figure figcaption {
    color: #9db8e8;
  }

  .feature-media img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .feature-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .feature-copy h3 {
    font-size: 1.45rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }

  .feature-copy p {
    font-size: 1.01rem;
  }

  .feature-copy p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .build {
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    padding-top: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .build-head {
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .build-title {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }

  .build-lead {
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .build-cta {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
  }

  .evidence {
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    padding-top: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .evidence-title {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }

  .evidence-lead {
    max-width: 62ch;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .evidence-grid {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 1.8rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .evidence-grid figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .evidence-media {
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--navy-900), var(--navy-800));
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }

  .evidence-media img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .evidence-media--light {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .evidence-media--light img {
    object-fit: contain;
  }

  .evidence-grid figcaption {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .loops {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .feature {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .feature--flip .feature-media {
      order: 0;
    }

    .evidence-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      max-width: 26rem;
    }
  }
</style>
